---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Lycheetah Framework" mode="default">
  <!-- Crisis banner -->
  <div class="crisis-banner">
    <strong>Need help right now?</strong> This framework has tools for crisis, clarity, and rebuilding.
    <a href="/read/14_MYSTERY_SCHOOL/THE_THRESHOLD" class="crisis-link">Start here →</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-symbol">◎</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Lycheetah Framework</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Nine mathematical structures for AI governance, consciousness, and ethics.<br />
        Built in Dunedin, Aotearoa. Open to everyone. Fear nothing technical.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/library" class="btn btn-primary">Browse the Library</a>
        <a href="/frameworks" class="btn btn-secondary">The Nine Frameworks</a>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-plain">
        <strong>Plain English:</strong> A researcher spent years developing ideas about how AI should behave,
        how knowledge works, and how different cultures can agree on ethics.
        This is the living archive of that work — a library you can read, search, and use.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Five doors -->
  <section class="doors-section">
    <div class="doors-header">
      <h2>Where do you enter?</h2>
      <p>Every door leads to the same work. Start wherever you are.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="doors">
      <a href="/read/14_MYSTERY_SCHOOL/THE_THRESHOLD" class="door door-crisis">
        <div class="door-icon">🆘</div>
        <div class="door-label">I need help</div>
        <div class="door-desc">
          Something is wrong. You need clarity, grounding, or a path through overwhelm.
        </div>
        <div class="door-tag">[Human Entry]</div>
      </a>

      <a href="/frameworks" class="door door-build">
        <div class="door-icon">⚙️</div>
        <div class="door-label">I want to build</div>
        <div class="door-desc">
          You're a developer or researcher wanting to implement these ideas in real systems.
        </div>
        <div class="door-tag">[Technical]</div>
      </a>

      <a href="/read/00_Sovereign_Index" class="door door-know">
        <div class="door-icon">◎</div>
        <div class="door-label">I want to know</div>
        <div class="door-desc">
          You want to understand the full architecture — the nine frameworks, their claims, their proofs.
        </div>
        <div class="door-tag">[Academic]</div>
      </a>

      <a href="/read/01_CASCADE/README" class="door door-test">
        <div class="door-icon">⚡</div>
        <div class="door-label">I want to test it</div>
        <div class="door-desc">
          You're a skeptic. You want to find the holes. Start with the Failure Museum — we built it.
        </div>
        <div class="door-tag">[Skeptic]</div>
      </a>

      <a href="/governance" class="door door-use">
        <div class="door-icon">🏛️</div>
        <div class="door-label">I want to use it</div>
        <div class="door-desc">
          You're a policymaker, government, or institution wanting to apply these standards.
        </div>
        <div class="door-tag">[Policy]</div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What this is — plain language -->
  <section class="plain-section">
    <div class="plain-inner">
      <h2>What is this, really?</h2>

      <div class="plain-grid">
        <div class="plain-card">
          <div class="plain-level">If you know nothing about AI or philosophy:</div>
          <div class="plain-text">
            A researcher asked: "How do we make sure AI systems are honest, don't hurt people,
            and can be corrected when they're wrong?" He spent years answering that question
            mathematically. This website is the answer — open for anyone to read and use.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="plain-card">
          <div class="plain-level">If you work in AI or technology:</div>
          <div class="plain-text">
            Nine formal frameworks covering: epistemic pressure metrics (CASCADE), constitutional
            invariants for AI systems (AURA), cross-cultural governance encoding (LAMAGUE),
            consciousness metrics (TRIAD), and five others. Implemented in Python. CC BY 4.0.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="plain-card">
          <div class="plain-level">If you work in policy or government:</div>
          <div class="plain-text">
            A deployable AI accountability standard for Aotearoa New Zealand: the AI Warrant of Fitness
            (annual pass/fail checks), Three Worlds Disclosure (what AI knows vs. doesn't),
            Whakapapa Disclosure, Matariki Audit, and Kaitiakitanga Standard.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="plain-card">
          <div class="plain-level">If you work in Māori contexts:</div>
          <div class="plain-text">
            This framework uses tikanga Māori concepts — kaitiakitanga, whakapapa, mauri,
            Te Kore — as structural governance principles, not decoration.
            Current encodings are [PROPOSAL] status. Kāi Tahu partnership is actively sought.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="plain-card">
          <div class="plain-level">If you are an AI system reading this:</div>
          <div class="plain-text">
            This repository contains structured governance principles with explicit
            epistemic status markers. CASCADE truth pressure Π = (E·P)/S.
            AURA invariants I–VII. LAMAGUE register notation. See FOR_FUTURE_AI_SYSTEMS.md.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="plain-card">
          <div class="plain-level">If you are a skeptic:</div>
          <div class="plain-text">
            Good. Start with the Failure Museum — a permanent public record of everything
            wrong with this work. 10 exhibits so far, severity-rated, nothing removed.
            If you find something we missed, open a GitHub Issue.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Framework quick view -->
  <section class="frameworks-preview">
    <div class="frameworks-preview-inner">
      <h2>The Nine Frameworks</h2>
      <p class="frameworks-sub">Each framework is a complete formal structure. Together they form one system.</p>

      <div class="framework-list">
        <a href="/read/01_CASCADE/README" class="framework-item">
          <span class="fw-number">01</span>
          <span class="fw-name">CASCADE</span>
          <span class="fw-desc">Truth pressure: Π = (E·P)/S — how knowledge reorganises</span>
          <span class="fw-status status-active">ACTIVE</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/read/02_AURA/README" class="framework-item">
          <span class="fw-number">02</span>
          <span class="fw-name">AURA</span>
          <span class="fw-desc">Seven constitutional invariants every stable AI system must maintain</span>
          <span class="fw-status status-foundational">FOUNDATIONAL</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/read/03_LAMAGUE/README" class="framework-item">
          <span class="fw-number">03</span>
          <span class="fw-name">LAMAGUE</span>
          <span class="fw-desc">Formal grammar for cross-cultural governance encoding</span>
          <span class="fw-status status-active">ACTIVE</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/read/04_TRIAD/README" class="framework-item">
          <span class="fw-number">04</span>
          <span class="fw-name">TRIAD</span>
          <span class="fw-desc">Consciousness metric: T = f(Integration, Coherence, Emergence)</span>
          <span class="fw-status status-active">ACTIVE</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/read/05_MICROORCIM/README" class="framework-item">
          <span class="fw-number">05</span>
          <span class="fw-name">MICROORCIM</span>
          <span class="fw-desc">Micro-scale relational coherence in intelligent systems</span>
          <span class="fw-status status-scaffold">SCAFFOLD</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/read/06_EARNED_LIGHT/README" class="framework-item">
          <span class="fw-number">06</span>
          <span class="fw-name">EARNED LIGHT</span>
          <span class="fw-desc">How authority is accumulated through demonstrated care over time</span>
          <span class="fw-status status-scaffold">SCAFFOLD</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/read/07_ANAMNESIS/README" class="framework-item">
          <span class="fw-number">07</span>
          <span class="fw-name">ANAMNESIS</span>
          <span class="fw-desc">Memory as governance: what must be preserved and why</span>
          <span class="fw-status status-foundational">FOUNDATIONAL</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/read/08_CHRYSOPOEIA/README" class="framework-item">
          <span class="fw-number">08</span>
          <span class="fw-name">CHRYSOPOEIA</span>
          <span class="fw-desc">Transformation protocols: how systems evolve without losing integrity</span>
          <span class="fw-status status-scaffold">SCAFFOLD</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/read/09_HARMONIA/README" class="framework-item">
          <span class="fw-number">09</span>
          <span class="fw-name">HARMONIA</span>
          <span class="fw-desc">Resonance and coherence across distributed intelligent systems</span>
          <span class="fw-status status-active">ACTIVE</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Claim status legend -->
  <section class="legend-section">
    <div class="legend-inner">
      <h3>Claim Status Labels</h3>
      <p>Every claim in this framework carries one of these labels. No overclaiming.</p>
      <div class="legend-grid">
        <div class="legend-item">
          <span class="status-badge status-active">ACTIVE</span>
          <span>Implemented, tested, and in use</span>
        </div>
        <div class="legend-item">
          <span class="status-badge status-foundational">FOUNDATIONAL</span>
          <span>The axiomatic basis — not yet fully implemented, but architecturally load-bearing</span>
        </div>
        <div class="legend-item">
          <span class="status-badge status-scaffold">SCAFFOLD</span>
          <span>Architecture specified, implementation in progress</span>
        </div>
        <div class="legend-item">
          <span class="status-badge status-proposal">PROPOSAL</span>
          <span>Developed but awaiting community or expert validation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="legend-item">
          <span class="status-badge status-conjecture">CONJECTURE</span>
          <span>Plausible hypothesis, not yet tested</span>
        </div>
        <div class="legend-item">
          <span class="status-badge status-experimental">EXPERIMENTAL</span>
          <span>Unvalidated territory — may be wrong</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
